Subject: [PATCH] stratum: accept EVM (0x…40-hex) wallet addresses for auxpow children

Yiimp's `coind_validate_address()` assumes a bitcoin-style base58 / bech32
address: it calls `validateaddress` on the coind, then `base58_decode`s
the wallet into `script_pubkey`, then falls back to the RPC's
`scriptPubKey` field. An EVM auxpow child (ZCU) served via a
bitcoind-compat adapter cannot satisfy any of those paths, so the coin
is marked invalid and never enters the aux merge-mine rotation.

For a pure-aux child (auxpow=1) stratum does NOT build the child
coinbase itself — the adapter's createauxblock / submitauxblock handles
the EVM side. Stratum only needs to:

  1. recognise a `0x` + 40-hex string as a valid payout target,
  2. store the 20-byte payload in `coind->script_pubkey`
     (hex form, 40 chars — matches how script_pubkey is used elsewhere),
  3. skip the RPC validation dance and return true.

Apply on the live tree, then rebuild + reinstall:

    cd /home/ubuntu/aws/LIVE/LIVE-FINAL/stratum
    sudo patch -p1 < /path/to/stratum-coind-evm.patch
    sudo make -j$(nproc)
    sudo install -m755 stratum /var/stratum/stratum
    sudo systemctl restart stratum-scrypt

---
 stratum/coind.cpp | 34 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 34 insertions(+)

--- a/stratum/coind.cpp
+++ b/stratum/coind.cpp
@@ -108,10 +108,44 @@ static void coind_error(YAAMP_COIND *coind, const char *s)
 	// (context lines — adjust if your local hunk anchor differs)
 }
 
+// --- EVM aux-child support ------------------------------------------------
+// Detect a 0x-prefixed 40-hex EVM address (e.g. 0xe3Aa…Bdfe).
+// Case-insensitive on the hex nibbles; checksum casing is not enforced
+// because EIP-55 checksums are advisory and coind adapters are free to
+// normalise them.
+static bool is_evm_address(const char *s)
+{
+	if (!s || strlen(s) != 42) return false;
+	if (s[0] != '0' || (s[1] != 'x' && s[1] != 'X')) return false;
+	for (int i = 2; i < 42; i++) {
+		char c = s[i];
+		if (!((c >= '0' && c <= '9') ||
+		      (c >= 'a' && c <= 'f') ||
+		      (c >= 'A' && c <= 'F'))) return false;
+	}
+	return true;
+}
+// --------------------------------------------------------------------------
+
 bool coind_validate_address(YAAMP_COIND *coind)
 {
 	if(!coind->wallet[0]) return false;
 
+	// EVM aux-child fast path: no base58, no validateaddress RPC.
+	// The bitcoind-compat adapter (createauxblock / submitauxblock) is
+	// responsible for the EVM-side coinbase payout to this address; we
+	// only need to stash the 20-byte payload so downstream code that
+	// touches coind->script_pubkey has a non-empty value.
+	if (is_evm_address(coind->wallet)) {
+		// store the 40 hex chars (drop the 0x) — this matches how the
+		// rest of the codebase treats script_pubkey (hex string).
+		strncpy(coind->script_pubkey, coind->wallet + 2,
+		        sizeof(coind->script_pubkey) - 1);
+		coind->script_pubkey[sizeof(coind->script_pubkey) - 1] = '\0';
+		coind->pubkey[0]  = '\0';
+		coind->account[0] = '\0';
+		coind->p2sh_address = false;
+		stratumlog("%s EVM wallet %s accepted (aux child, adapter handles coinbase)\n",
+		           coind->symbol, coind->wallet);
+		return true;
+	}
+
 	char params[YAAMP_SMALLBUFSIZE];
 	sprintf(params, "[\"%s\"]", coind->wallet);
 
